image.altText: A smartphone with an Airbnb logo on it in front of the same logo being projected on a screen.

props.synopsis: Short-stay accommodation provider Airbnb is fined $15 million for tricking tens of thousands of customers into paying higher prices for years by falsely charging them in US dollars.

title.children: Airbnb fined $15 million for tricking thousands of Australians into paying higher prices for years

image.altText: A school photo of a teenaged boy

props.synopsis: Sixteen-year-old Lachlan Cook died in Melbourne's Royal Children's Hospital in 2019 after an emergency flight home from the Kilvington Grammar School trip.

title.children: School's 'laissez-faire' attitude contributed to death of diabetic student Lachlan Cook on 2019 school trip, coroner says

image.altText: A soldier helps a lady onto the aircraft

props.synopsis: Police say the man's house in Degarra has been "washed away" with no sign of him since Sunday, as emergency crews still managing recovery on the north tropical coast evacuate residents from Cape York.

title.children: Grave concerns for missing man in Far North Queensland as flooding threat turns to Cape York

image.altText: A large building surrounded by smoke

props.synopsis: Residents in a small town in WA's Wheatbelt are warned to act immediately to survive as a bushfire threatens the area, about 85 kilometres north-east of Perth.

title.children: Bushfire north-east of Perth threatens lives as residents warned it's too late to leave, fire truck rolls over

image.altText: Woman in a white top sitting next to a man in a green shirt. There's a bookcase and Christmas tree behind them.

props.synopsis: An accident left Elliott Shaw with two severed arteries, damaged nerves and tendons. He and his wife are now speaking out after they couldn't get an ambulance in an emergency.

title.children: A Brisbane dad nearly lost his hand after a freak accident, but no ambulance was available

image.altText: An elderly caucasian in a blue suit, red tie, speaking into a microphone with an American flag in the background.

props.synopsis: The court declares former US president Donald Trump ineligible for the White House under the constitution's insurrection clause for his role in the January 6, 2021, attack on the US Capitol.

title.children: Colorado Supreme Court bans Trump from the state's presidential ballot

image.altText: Jadd William Brooker

props.synopsis: Adelaide paedophile Jadd William Brooker, who committed some of "the worst and most degrading offending" seen by investigating police, has been handed a 36-year sentence.

title.children: Notorious Adelaide paedophile sentenced to 36 years in jail for child sex offending

image.altText: Australian Prime Minister Anthony Albanese and partner Jodie Haydon standing and waving as they board the plane.

title.children: Politician expenses revealed for first months of Albanese government

image.altText: Man wearing white Islamic cap with long brown beard gestures toward washing line with fence and brick home in background

props.synopsis: Attorney-General Mark Dreyfus accuses acting Opposition Leader Sussan Ley of stoking fear in the community over the release of a convicted terrorist from jail.

title.children: Attorney-general says criticism over terrorist's release 'nonsensical' as opposition calls for his dumping

image.altText: Covid germs hover over a graph on a black background

image.altText: Two women walking next to each other on the street. They are wearing face masks and jackets

title.children: New COVID-19 strain labelled 'variant of interest' by World Health Organization

image.altText: The Galaxy Leader cargo ship is escorted by Houthi boats in the Red Sea in this photo released November 20, 2023.

title.children: Rebels with drones are sending billions of dollars of cargo on an expensive 10-day detour and you may pay the price

image.altText: PM Anthony Albanese shakes hands with NZ PM Christopher Luxon in a warm greeting in front of flags from the two countries

title.children: AUKUS and Māori relations feature in Albanese's first joint appearance with NZ PM Luxon

image.altText: A close up of Mel Schilling wearing a white blazer with feathery trim at the sleeves

props.synopsis: Mel Schilling says she originally thought her stomach was hurting because she'd been travelling so much, but knew something "still wasn't right". A scan revealed she had a 5 centimetre tumour.

title.children: Married at First Sight star urges people not to ignore symptoms after stomach cramps turn out to be colon cancer

image.altText: A topless man is arrested by police officers next to a car

image.altText: A close up photo of Anna smiling against a blue sky

title.children: Axe attacker admits attempting to murder federal MP Kate Chaney's sister at Perth medical clinic

image.altText: New laws for criminal bikie gangs

image.altText: A middle-aged man with grey-white hair wearing a grey T-shirt looks serious in front of a plain background.

props.synopsis: Those set to be identified range from high-profile associates, including at least one public figure whose name is said to have appeared in Epstein's infamous "little black book", to innocent people mentioned in deposition transcripts.

image.altText: A man in a suit and a woman in black with arms around each other leaning on ballet barre

image.altText: A composite of two images: One of a woman holding a coloured glass bottle/vase and smiling, the other of said vase on display

title.children: Jessica bought this op shop vase for $6, before realising it was rare. It just sold for $150,000

image.altText: An image of a cat lying on a couch looking at a laser dot on its fabric, surrounded by video test pattern graphics

props.synopsis: The owner of an orange tabby cat called Taters is celebrating after a video of the feline was sent to Earth from 31 million kilometres away.

title.children: This cat video has made history by being sent to Earth through 31 million kilometres of deep space

image.altText: A framed picture of a man on a glass table

props.synopsis: When Yuval heard the shots ring out, he jumped out of his car and raced into the fray. But a tragic case of mistaken identity left him bleeding to death on the street.

title.children: An Israeli reservist thought he killed a Hamas terrorist. The man's true identity has rocked a nation

image.altText: A young woman wearing a blue shirt stares sadly at the camera

props.synopsis: Mount Isa's Gemma Catchpole is proud to call the outback home, but feels let down by authorities after being targeted by thieves. She's calling for victims to "stand together" and demand action on youth crime.

image.altText: An unidentified person standing on an electric scooter with other scooters parked nearby.

props.synopsis: The state's transport department is looking into ways to further address drink riding, in an effort to protect road and footpath users.

title.children: Random breath testing could be on the way for Queensland e-scooter riders and cyclists

image.altText: Woman wearing red lipstick and red hairband with flower.

props.synopsis: Italian immigrant Saman Abbas, 18, was killed in 2021, after a picture of her kissing her boyfriend enraged her parents, who insisted she enter an arranged marriage.

title.children: Parents sentenced to life in jail after killing daughter who refused arranged marriage

image.altText: Ajla Tomljanović plays a forehand return

props.synopsis: After missing 10 months of tennis following knee surgery, Ajla Tomljanović is confident she can scale the heights again and be a contender at the majors, starting at January's Australian Open at Melbourne Park.

title.children: Returning Tomljanović focused on self-belief ahead of Australian Open

image.altText: a family walks down the side of a closed highway carrying bags of belongings

image.altText: A white and purple passenger plane on a runway.

title.children: Budget carrier Bonza works to build trust after weeks of cancellations

image.altText: A mix of cars and trucks fill four lanes of peak hour traffic on freeway.

image.altText: A woman in a black t-shirt and white hat holds a papaya fruit hanging in a tree.

props.synopsis: Far North Queensland growers are reporting major losses to Cyclone Jasper and torrential rain as the tropical fruit season peaks for Christmas, including sweeping damage across mango orchards.

title.children: Fruit growers plead for help from consumers, prime minister as flooding cleanup begins
